review_blob:
From bottle. Brown medium high head.
Distinct aroma of tar. Taste is too much tar for my taste. The cocoa is in the background but the typical cocoa-dryness is noticable in the mouthfeel. Decent, not great.
So thick as IT pours, almost like grapefruit-lemonade. Fresh taste. Low bur existeng tart- and dryness. Really interesting and awesome beer!

Head doesnt last long, some lacing on the glass though. Really clear with medium copper colour. Not really fair by judging this beer right now because i have a cold so.. Will probably go back on this one.
Reminds of a straight wheatbeer. Tasty!............................... Good one
Bottle. Clear golden beer with a small head. Yeast and hops in aroma. Decent!
Hoppy aroma and a head that lasts some time. Nice taste but doesnt last that long.
Nice golden color with creamy coloured head. Tastes caramel and comfortably hoppy. Nice Ale!
Overall a decent beer, i had it to some steak and it's flavours really came through in a different way. It fitted perfectly to the steak.
Comfortably tart and dry. I get some citrus in the aftertaste. Refreshing and something i would enjoy even more in the summer.
Lovely foamy warm white head. Mouthfeel is smooth but not oily. Slightly burnt taste but alot of dark fruits also. Warm finish with lingering taste. Great!
Bottle. Wheaty aroma, quite nice. Taste is quite anonymous, watery mouthfeel and if there even is an aftertaste its bready. Not something i will try again.
Maltig smak med ganska ltt kropp. Behaglig till mat och en totalt sett en rtt okej folkl!
Russintoner, ganska ltt kolsyrad vilket passade bra och behaglig vrme i eftersmaken. God l!
Pretty good and looking forward to store some bottles to see their development.
